gh-delete-workflow-runs - GitHub Workflow Run Deleter

USAGE:
    gh-delete-workflow-runs <repository-owner> <repository> [filter]

DESCRIPTION:
    Delete GitHub Actions workflow runs for specified repository.
    Supports filtering by branch or custom criteria.

ARGUMENTS:
    repository-owner
        Repository owner (required)

    repository
        Repository name (required)

    filter
        Filter criteria for workflow runs (optional):
        select(expression) - Custom jq filter
        =branch - Filter by exact branch name
        *branch* - Filter by branch pattern

CONFIGURATION:
    -conf-gh-delete-workflow-parallel-runs NUM
        Parallel deletion requests (default: 10)

EXAMPLES:
    gh-delete-workflow-runs owner repo
    gh-delete-workflow-runs owner repo feature-branch
    gh-delete-workflow-runs owner repo "select(.head_branch != \"main\")"
